<div class="row">
  <div class="col-auto">
    <h2>Welcome, {{user.name}}!</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div>


    <div class="search-container">
    

          <input class="searchbar" id="user-input" type="text" placeholder="Search.." name="search">

          <button type="submit" id="search-button"><i class="fa fa-search"></i></button>


    </form>

  </div>

  <div>

    <select class="form-control browser-default dropdown" id="ratio-choice" onchange="changeSelect()">
              {{!-- <option value="" selected="selected">Choose Ratio</option> --}}
              <option value="1">Current Ratio</option>
              <option value="2">Working Capital</option>
              <option value="3">Quick Ratio</option>
            </select>

  </div>  

      
    <div>

      {{!-- chart --}}
        <canvas id="myChart" width="800" height="400"></canvas>

    </div>

    <div id="ratioText">The current ratio is a liquidity ratio that measures a companys ability to pay short-term obligations or those due within one year. It tells investors and analysts how a company can maximize the current assets on its balance sheet to satisfy its current debt and other payables. A current ratio that is in line with the industry average or slightly higher is generally considered acceptable. A current ratio that is lower than the industry average may indicate a higher risk of distress or default. Similarly, if a company has a very high current ratio compared with its peer group, it indicates that management may not be using its assets efficiently.</div>

</div>


<!-- Enter Company Name -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-auto">
    <form>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="ticker">Portfolio:</label>
        <input class="form-control" type="text" id="user-input" name="ticker" required value="AAPL">
      </div>
      <button id="add-button" class="form-control btn btn-search">Add</button>
      <hr class="my-4">
      <!-- Show Portfolio List -->
      {{#if user.portfolios.length}}
      <div class="form-group">
          {{#each user.portfolios as |portfolio| }}
          <label for="portfolio-checkbox">
            <input type="checkbox" class="single-check" data-id="{{portfolio.company_symbol}}" name="portfolio-checkbox" onclick="onlyOne(this)" /> {{portfolio.company_symbol}}
          </label>
          {{/each}}
      </div>
      <button id="delete-button" class="form-control btn btn-danger">Delete</button>
      {{/if}}
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
      
{{#if user.portfolios.length}}
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-auto">
    <p class="text-center"> Company Information </p>
  </div>
</div>

<button id="company-button" class="btn btn-primary">Information</button>
<button id="result-button" class="btn btn-primary">Result Button</button>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-auto">
    <div class="card">
      {{#each user.portfolios as |portfolio| }}
      <div class="card-header">
        <h4>Company: {{portfolio.company_symbol}}</h4>
        <p></p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text">{{portfolio.description}}</p>
      </div>
      {{/each}}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{{/if}}



    
